comments: Brooks (MEM) is already in Reaves' (LAL) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Russell (LAL) makes contact with Bane's (MEM) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) is already in Tillman's (MEM) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Morant (MEM) is moving alongside Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.  The shot is then cleanly blocked by Jackson Jr. (MEM).
Jackson Jr (MEM) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Los Angeles.
Bane (MEM) legally contests Hachimura's (LAL) jump shot attempt.

As Schroder (LAL) turns to spin off of the pick, he and Brooks (MEM) make incidental head to head contact with one another on the perimeter.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
James (LAL) lowers his arm and makes contact with Morant's (MEM) head prior to making any contact with the ball.
James (LAL) clamps and holds Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm, which affects his pursuit of the rebound.
James (LAL) does not put part of his hand under the ball, and either carry it from one point to another or bring it to a pause and then continue to dribble again.
Schroder (LAL) is already in Tillman's (MEM) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Bane (MEM) is retreating his arm away from Reaves' (LAL) path, and the contact to Reaves' left shoulder during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Hachimura (LAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Morant's (MEM) driving shot attempt.
Hachimura (LAL) is already in Tillman's (MEM) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Tillman (MEM) is moving alongside James' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.

Tillman (MEM) contests Hachimura's (LAL) shot near the rim, and his hand makes some contact with Hachimura's head after Jackson Jr. (MEM) blocks the shot attempt.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Reaves (LAL) moves slightly forward towards Morant (MEM) and marginal contact occurs as Morant is passing the ball.
Tillman (MEM) moves alongside James' (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) cleanly blocks Morant's (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Reaves (LAL) is already in Brooks' (MEM) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Bane (MEM) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Los Angeles.
Davis (LAL) brings his hands towards Bane (MEM) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away towards the basket.
Tillman (MEM) is moving alongside Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) brings his hands towards Davis' (LAL) upper body and marginal contact occurs during the put back attempt.
Morant (MEM) is firming up in Reaves' (LAL) path and he absorbs the contact.  Additionally, Tillman (MEM) is also firming up and does not deliver contact during the pick.
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Morant's (MEM) path and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Tillman (MEM) cleanly deflects the ball away from Davis (LAL).
Brooks (MEM) extends his forearm into James' (LAL) body and initiates contact as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) is firming up over his left leg and absorbs the contact from Schroder (LAL) during the screen.
Hachimura (LAL) legally contests Morant's (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Tillman (MEM) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Los Angeles.
Tillman (MEM) commits a take foul on Schroder (LAL).
Morant (MEM) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Schroder (LAL) cleanly dislodges the ball from Jackson Jr. (MEM).  Any ensuing arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
After the ball is dislodged by Schroder (LAL), Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) momentum carries him into the backcourt and he legally regains possession.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Brooks' (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Brooks (MEM) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL).
